# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Personal Context Bot — Configuration
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your values:
#   cp .env.example .env
#
# Lines starting with # are comments. Uncomment and
# edit the ones you need.
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════

# ── 1. Calendar URLs (at least one required) ──

# Uncomment and set the calendars you use.
# See SETUP.md section 3 for how to get each URL.
#
# Each calendar has a label that appears in the LLM context
# (e.g. "[Work] Team standup") and determines work vs personal
# classification. See WORK_LABELS below.

# iCloud (webcal:// or https://)
# ICLOUD_URL=webcal://p60-caldav.icloud.com/published/2/YOUR_ID_HERE
# ICLOUD_LABEL=Personal

# Outlook 365
# OUTLOOK_URL=https://outlook.office365.com/owa/calendar/YOUR_CALENDAR_ID/calendar.ics
# OUTLOOK_LABEL=Work

# Google Calendar (Settings → calendar → Integrate → Secret address in iCal format)
# GOOGLE_URL=https://calendar.google.com/calendar/ical/YOUR_ID/basic.ics
# GOOGLE_LABEL=Google

# Extra calendars — any ICS URL (up to 9: CALENDAR_1 through CALENDAR_9)
# CALENDAR_1_URL=https://example.com/feed.ics
# CALENDAR_1_LABEL=Family

# ── 2. Discord Bot (optional — omit for notification-only mode) ──

# Enables interactive LLM chat via Discord DM or channel.
# See SETUP.md section 2 for how to create a bot and get these values.
# DISCORD_BOT_TOKEN=
# DISCORD_CHANNEL_ID=

# ── 2b. Discord Access Control (optional) ──

# Restrict the bot to specific Discord users (comma-separated user IDs).
# If unset, the bot responds to anyone who can DM it or post in the channel.
# To get a user ID: Discord → User Settings → Advanced → Developer Mode,
# then right-click a user → Copy User ID.
# DISCORD_ALLOWED_USERS=123456789012345678,987654321098765432

# ── 3. Notifications (required if scheduled digests are enabled) ──

# Apprise URL — used by the weeknight and weekend digest notifications.
# Not needed if you set both WEEKNIGHT_SCHEDULE=off and WEEKEND_SCHEDULE=off.
#
# Discord webhook: discord://webhook_id/webhook_token
#   (See SETUP.md section 4 for how to create one)
# Telegram: tgram://bottoken/chatid
# All 90+ services: https://github.com/caronc/apprise/wiki
# APPRISE_URL=discord://webhook_id/webhook_token

# ── 4. Ollama LLM ──

# Docker: use host.docker.internal (default — reaches host from container)
# Local (no Docker): use localhost
# Separate machine (NAS setup): use the LAN IP (see NAS-DUAL-SETUP.md)
OLLAMA_URL=http://host.docker.internal:11434
OLLAMA_MODEL=gemma4:e4b

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Optional — everything below has sensible defaults
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════

# Timezone (IANA format — https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_tz_database_time_zones)
# TZ=America/Los_Angeles

# ── Scheduled Digests ──
# Format: "days HH:MM" or "off" to disable
# Days use APScheduler names: mon,tue,wed,thu,fri,sat,sun
#
# Weeknight digest — sends tomorrow's WORK calendar events
# WEEKNIGHT_SCHEDULE=sun,mon,tue,wed,thu 20:00
#
# Weekend preview — sends Fri/Sat/Sun events from ALL calendars
# WEEKEND_SCHEDULE=thu 16:00
#
# Examples:
#   WEEKNIGHT_SCHEDULE=mon,tue,wed,thu,fri 21:00   (weekdays at 9 PM)
#   WEEKEND_SCHEDULE=wed 17:30                      (Wednesday at 5:30 PM)
#   WEEKNIGHT_SCHEDULE=off                          (disable entirely)

# ── Work vs Personal ──
# Which calendar labels count as "work" (comma-separated).
# Controls two things:
#   1. Weeknight digest only includes events from these calendars
#   2. LLM is told which calendars are work vs personal
# Default: Work (matches OUTLOOK_LABEL default)
# WORK_LABELS=Work
#
# To mark multiple calendars as work:
# WORK_LABELS=Work,Freelance

# ── Event Filtering ──
# Hide events from digests AND LLM context (comma-separated, case-insensitive).
# Any event whose title contains a substring here will be excluded.
# IGNORED_EVENTS=pick up kids,drop off kids,lunch

# ── LLM Settings ──

# How many days of calendar data the LLM can see (default: 7)
# More days = more context but slightly slower responses
# CONTEXT_DAYS=7

# Calendar cache duration in seconds (default: 3600 = 1 hour)
# CACHE_TTL=3600

# Override the LLM system prompt. Calendar data is appended automatically —
# you only set the instruction/personality portion here.
# SYSTEM_PROMPT=You are Friday, a sarcastic but helpful calendar assistant. Keep answers short and witty.
